using (who) can tell you whos logged into the machine

using (ifconfig) gives you IP and physical address information

using (netstat) -ano gives you network connection information *helps find suspisious ports

using (sudo netstat -ltup gives the process ID associated with the certain connection.

use ls -l to look at file permissions drxwr-x-r-x first bit (d) means its a directory a (-) is a file
the next group of bits (rxw) is the next set r-w is the user permissions and the third (r-x) is the group permissions

(echo $directory 1> newfile) this command will send the output into the new file

the id command give info on current user

to find a user home directory sudo cat /etc/passwd to see the users home directories
